Maintains a climate-controlled vault for his rare butterfly collection next to his Bloomberg terminal. Claims the flight patterns of the Queen Alexandra's Birdwing predict widening credit spreads better than any algo. Do not touch the glass.
Talks about 'convexity' the way poets talk about love. Likely to short the office furniture if given the chance.
Thinks compliance rules are 'suggestions' for people with low beta. Will argue about the definition of EBITDA for hours.
Wears a vest regardless of the temperature or occasion. Whispers 'buy the dip' in their sleep.
